.TH "calc_dsc_bytes_per_pixel" 9 "calc_dsc_bytes_per_pixel" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
calc_dsc_bytes_per_pixel \- calculate bytes per pixel
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "u32" calc_dsc_bytes_per_pixel
.BI "(const struct drm_dsc_config *pps "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "pps" 12
DRM struct with all required DSC values
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Based on the information inside drm_dsc_config, this function calculates the
total of bytes per pixel.

\fInote\fP This calculation requires float point operation, most of it executes
under kernel_fpu_{begin,end}.
.SH "RETURN"
Return the number of bytes per pixel
